<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Free Payroll Tax Calculator 2025 | MyTaxCalcs</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Free payroll tax calculator for 2025. Estimate federal withholding, Social Security tax, Medicare tax, state withholding, and net take-home pay per paycheck.">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="canonical" href="<%= canonical %>">
  <meta property="og:title" content="Free Payroll Tax Calculator 2025 | MyTaxCalcs">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Estimate paycheck withholding, Social Security, Medicare, state withholding, and net pay for 2025.">
  <meta property="og:url" content="<%= canonical %>">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <meta property="og:site_name" content="MyTaxCalcs">
  <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary">
  <meta name="twitter:title" content="Free Payroll Tax Calculator 2025 | MyTaxCalcs">
  <meta name="twitter:description" content="Estimate your 2025 paycheck taxes and take-home pay for free.">
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="any">
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml">
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/favicon.png">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-FS9HCDT0D7"></script>
  <script>window.dataLayer=window.dataLayer||[];function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}gtag('js',new Date());gtag('config','G-FS9HCDT0D7');</script>
  <script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5193834725888549" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <style>
    .breadcrumb{max-width:780px;margin:0 auto;padding:14px 24px 0;font-size:.8rem;color:#6b7280;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap}
    .breadcrumb a{color:#16a34a;text-decoration:none}.breadcrumb a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
    .breadcrumb-sep{color:#d1d5db;font-size:.75rem}
    .calc-page{max-width:780px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px 60px}
    .calc-page-header{padding:28px 0 24px}
    .page-eyebrow{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;font-size:.75rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em;color:#e11d48;background:#fff1f2;border-radius:20px;padding:4px 12px;margin-bottom:12px}
    .calc-page-header h1{font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin:0 0 10px;color:#111827}
    .calc-page-header p{font-size:1rem;color:#6b7280;margin:0;max-width:580px}
    .calc-card-form{background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:16px;padding:32px;margin-bottom:24px;box-shadow:0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,.06)}
    .calc-card-form h2{font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827;margin:0 0 20px}
    .form-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:16px}
    @media(max-width:580px){.form-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
    .form-field{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:5px}
    .form-field.full{grid-column:1/-1}
    .form-field label{font-size:.82rem;font-weight:600;color:#374151}
    .input-wrap{position:relative;display:flex;align-items:center}
    .input-prefix{position:absolute;left:12px;font-size:.95rem;color:#9ca3af;pointer-events:none}
    .input-wrap input{padding-left:28px}
    .form-field input,.form-field select{border:1px solid #d1d5db;border-radius:8px;padding:9px 13px;font-size:.95rem;color:#111827;background:#f9fafb;transition:border-color .15s;width:100%;box-sizing:border-box}
    .form-field input:focus,.form-field select:focus{outline:none;border-color:#16a34a;background:#fff}
    .form-actions{margin-top:22px}
    .btn-calc{background:#16a34a;color:#fff;border:none;border-radius:10px;padding:12px 28px;font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;cursor:pointer;transition:background .15s,transform .1s;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:8px}
    .btn-calc:hover{background:#15803d;transform:translateY(-1px)}
    .result-card{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#f0fdf4 0%,#dcfce7 100%);border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:16px;padding:28px 32px;margin-bottom:24px}
    .result-card-header{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:20px}
    .result-icon{width:38px;height:38px;background:#16a34a;border-radius:10px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center}
    .result-card-header h2{font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:#14532d;margin:0}
    .result-primary{background:#fff;border-radius:12px;padding:20px 24px;margin-bottom:16px}
    .result-primary .result-label{font-size:.85rem;font-weight:600;color:#6b7280;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;display:block;margin-bottom:4px}
    .result-primary .result-amount{font-size:2.4rem;font-weight:800;color:#15803d}
    .result-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:12px}
    @media(max-width:520px){.result-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
    .result-item{background:#fff;border-radius:10px;padding:14px 16px}
    .result-item .ri-label{font-size:.78rem;color:#6b7280;font-weight:500;margin-bottom:3px}
    .result-item .ri-value{font-size:1.15rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827}
    .result-item .ri-value.red{color:#dc2626}
    .ad-zone{text-align:center;margin:28px 0;min-height:90px}
    .ad-zone-label{font-size:.7rem;color:#9ca3af;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em;margin-bottom:4px}
    .hiw-section{margin:48px 0 0}
    .section-eyebrow{font-size:.75rem;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em;color:#16a34a;margin-bottom:8px}
    .hiw-section h2,.faq-section h2,.related-section h2{font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin:0 0 8px}
    .hiw-section>p{color:#6b7280;margin:0 0 24px;font-size:.95rem}
    .hiw-steps{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:16px;margin-bottom:24px}
    .hiw-step{display:flex;gap:16px;align-items:flex-start;background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px}
    .hiw-step-num{min-width:32px;height:32px;background:#f0fdf4;border:2px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:.85rem;font-weight:800;color:#16a34a}
    .hiw-step-body h3{font-size:.9rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827;margin:0 0 4px}
    .hiw-step-body p{font-size:.85rem;color:#6b7280;margin:0}
    .formula-box{background:#111827;border-radius:12px;padding:20px 24px;margin-bottom:24px;overflow-x:auto}
    .formula-box-label{font-size:.7rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.1em;color:#6b7280;margin-bottom:10px}
    .formula-box code{font-family:'Courier New',monospace;font-size:.85rem;color:#d1fae5;line-height:1.7;display:block;white-space:pre}
    .formula-box code .comment{color:#4b5563}.formula-box code .highlight{color:#34d399}
    .faq-section{margin:48px 0 0}
    .faq-section h2{margin-bottom:20px}
    .faq-list{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px}
    .faq-item{background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden}
    .faq-question{width:100%;background:none;border:none;padding:17px 20px;text-align:left;font-size:.92rem;font-weight:600;color:#111827;cursor:pointer;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:12px}
    .faq-question:hover{background:#f9fafb}
    .faq-chevron{min-width:20px;height:20px;border-radius:50%;background:#f3f4f6;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;transition:transform .2s}
    .faq-item.open .faq-chevron{transform:rotate(180deg);background:#dcfce7}
    .faq-answer{display:none;padding:0 20px 17px;font-size:.88rem;color:#6b7280;line-height:1.65}
    .faq-item.open .faq-answer{display:block}
    .related-section{margin:48px 0 0}
    .related-section h2{margin-bottom:16px}
    .related-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px}
    @media(max-width:580px){.related-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}}
    @media(max-width:380px){.related-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
    .related-card{background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;padding:18px 16px;text-decoration:none;color:inherit;transition:border-color .15s,box-shadow .15s,transform .15s;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px}
    .related-card:hover{border-color:#16a34a;box-shadow:0 4px 12px rgba(22,163,74,.1);transform:translateY(-2px)}
    .related-card-icon{width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:9px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:2px}
    .related-card strong{font-size:.88rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827}
    .related-card span{font-size:.78rem;color:#9ca3af}
    .page-disclaimer{margin:40px 0 0;background:#f9fafb;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;padding:16px 20px;display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start}
    .page-disclaimer svg{color:#9ca3af;min-width:18px;margin-top:1px}
    .page-disclaimer p{font-size:.82rem;color:#6b7280;margin:0;line-height:1.55}
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header class="site-header">
    <nav class="nav">
      <a href="/" class="logo">
        <span class="logo-mark">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <rect x="1" y="1" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e"/>
            <rect x="11" y="1" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.5"/>
            <rect x="1" y="11" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.5"/>
            <rect x="11" y="11" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.25"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
        <span>MyTaxCalcs</span>
      </a>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/calculators">Calculators</a>
        <a href="/california-income-tax-calculator">States</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
      </div>
      <a class="nav-cta" href="/calculators">All Calculators</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <span class="breadcrumb-sep">&#8250;</span>
    <a href="/calculators">Calculators</a>
    <span class="breadcrumb-sep">&#8250;</span>
    <span>Payroll Tax Calculator</span>
  </nav>

  <main>
    <div class="calc-page">

      <div class="calc-page-header">
        <div class="page-eyebrow">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><rect x="2" y="7" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M16 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2h-4a2 2 0 00-2 2v16"/></svg>
          Paycheck Tax Estimator
        </div>
        <h1>Payroll Tax Calculator</h1>
        <p>Estimate federal withholding, Social Security tax, Medicare tax, optional state withholding, and take-home pay per paycheck for 2025.</p>
      </div>

      <% if (result) { %>
      <div class="result-card">
        <div class="result-card-header">
          <div class="result-icon">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="7" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M16 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2h-4a2 2 0 00-2 2v16"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h2>Your Paycheck Estimate</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="result-primary">
          <span class="result-label">Estimated Net Pay</span>
          <span class="result-amount">$<%= result.netPay.toFixed(2) %></span>
        </div>
        <div class="result-grid">
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Gross Pay</div>
            <div class="ri-value">$<%= result.grossPay.toFixed(2) %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Federal Withholding Est.</div>
            <div class="ri-value red">$<%= result.estimatedFederalWithholding.toFixed(2) %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Social Security Tax</div>
            <div class="ri-value red">$<%= result.socialSecurityTax.toFixed(2) %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Medicare Tax</div>
            <div class="ri-value red">$<%= result.medicareTax.toFixed(2) %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">State Withholding Est.</div>
            <div class="ri-value red">$<%= result.stateWithholding.toFixed(2) %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Total Taxes This Check</div>
            <div class="ri-value red">$<%= result.totalTaxes.toFixed(2) %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Est. Annual Net Pay</div>
            <div class="ri-value">$<%= result.estimatedAnnualNetPay.toFixed(2) %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Additional Medicare Tax</div>
            <div class="ri-value">$<%= result.additionalMedicareTax.toFixed(2) %></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ad-zone">
        <div class="ad-zone-label">Advertisement</div>
        <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block"
          data-ad-client="ca-pub-5193834725888549"
          data-ad-slot="5205436277"
          data-ad-format="auto"
          data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
        <script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
      </div>
      <% } %>

      <div class="calc-card-form">
        <h2>Enter Your Paycheck Information</h2>
        <form method="POST" action="/payroll-tax-calculator">
          <div class="form-grid">
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="grossPay">Gross Pay Per Paycheck</label>
              <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="grossPay" name="grossPay" min="0" step="0.01" value="<%= form.grossPay || '' %>" placeholder="2500.00" required>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="payFrequency">Pay Frequency</label>
              <select id="payFrequency" name="payFrequency">
                <option value="weekly" <%= form.payFrequency === 'weekly' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Weekly</option>
                <option value="biweekly" <%= (!form.payFrequency || form.payFrequency === 'biweekly') ? 'selected' : '' %>>Biweekly</option>
                <option value="semimonthly" <%= form.payFrequency === 'semimonthly' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Semi-monthly</option>
                <option value="monthly" <%= form.payFrequency === 'monthly' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Monthly</option>
                <option value="annual" <%= form.payFrequency === 'annual' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Annual</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="filingStatus">Filing Status</label>
              <select id="filingStatus" name="filingStatus">
                <option value="single" <%= (!form.filingStatus || form.filingStatus === 'single') ? 'selected' : '' %>>Single</option>
                <option value="marriedJoint" <%= form.filingStatus === 'marriedJoint' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Married Filing Jointly</option>
                <option value="marriedSeparate" <%= form.filingStatus === 'marriedSeparate' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Married Filing Separately</option>
                <option value="headHousehold" <%= form.filingStatus === 'headHousehold' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Head of Household</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="preTaxDeductions">Pre-Tax Deductions Per Paycheck</label>
              <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="preTaxDeductions" name="preTaxDeductions" min="0" step="0.01" value="<%= form.preTaxDeductions || '' %>" placeholder="200.00">
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="postTaxDeductions">Post-Tax Deductions Per Paycheck</label>
              <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="postTaxDeductions" name="postTaxDeductions" min="0" step="0.01" value="<%= form.postTaxDeductions || '' %>" placeholder="0.00">
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="federalExtraWithholding">Extra Federal Withholding Per Paycheck</label>
              <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="federalExtraWithholding" name="federalExtraWithholding" min="0" step="0.01" value="<%= form.federalExtraWithholding || '' %>" placeholder="0.00">
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="stateTaxRate">State Withholding Rate (%)</label>
              <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">%</span>
                <input type="number" id="stateTaxRate" name="stateTaxRate" min="0" step="0.001" value="<%= form.stateTaxRate || '' %>" placeholder="5.0">
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="ytdWagesBeforeThisPaycheck">Year-to-Date Wages Before This Check</label>
              <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="ytdWagesBeforeThisPaycheck" name="ytdWagesBeforeThisPaycheck" min="0" step="0.01" value="<%= form.ytdWagesBeforeThisPaycheck || '' %>" placeholder="0.00">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="form-actions">
            <button type="submit" class="btn-calc">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="7" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M16 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2h-4a2 2 0 00-2 2v16"/></svg>
              Calculate Payroll Taxes
            </button>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>

      <div class="hiw-section">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">How It Works</div>
        <h2>How Payroll Taxes Are Calculated</h2>
        <p>Every paycheck has several layers of tax deductions. Here is the order in which they are applied.</p>
        <div class="hiw-steps">
          <div class="hiw-step">
            <div class="hiw-step-num">1</div>
            <div class="hiw-step-body">
              <h3>Subtract Pre-Tax Deductions</h3>
              <p>Pre-tax deductions like 401(k) contributions and health insurance premiums reduce your taxable pay before federal withholding is calculated.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hiw-step">
            <div class="hiw-step-num">2</div>
            <div class="hiw-step-body">
              <h3>Estimate Federal Withholding</h3>
              <p>Your annualized taxable pay is run through 2025 federal tax brackets based on your filing status. The result is divided back to per-paycheck withholding.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hiw-step">
            <div class="hiw-step-num">3</div>
            <div class="hiw-step-body">
              <h3>Calculate FICA Taxes</h3>
              <p>Social Security tax is 6.2% up to the annual wage base ($176,100 for 2025). Medicare tax is 1.45% on all wages, plus an additional 0.9% above $200,000.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hiw-step">
            <div class="hiw-step-num">4</div>
            <div class="hiw-step-body">
              <h3>Subtract All Deductions for Net Pay</h3>
              <p>Federal withholding, FICA taxes, state withholding, and post-tax deductions are all subtracted from gross pay to estimate your take-home amount.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="formula-box">
          <div class="formula-box-label">Formula Reference</div>
          <code><span class="comment">// FICA Rates (2025)</span>
<span class="highlight">Social Security</span>  = Taxable Wages x 6.2%  (up to $176,100 YTD)
<span class="highlight">Medicare</span>         = Taxable Wages x 1.45% (no wage base limit)
<span class="highlight">Add. Medicare</span>    = Wages above $200,000 x 0.9%

<span class="comment">// Net Pay</span>
<span class="highlight">Taxable Pay</span>      = Gross Pay - Pre-Tax Deductions
<span class="highlight">Net Pay</span>          = Gross Pay - Federal WH - SS - Medicare - State WH - Post-Tax</code>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ad-zone">
        <div class="ad-zone-label">Advertisement</div>
        <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block"
          data-ad-client="ca-pub-5193834725888549"
          data-ad-slot="4212978293"
          data-ad-format="auto"
          data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
        <script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-section">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">FAQ</div>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">What taxes usually come out of a paycheck?<span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-answer">Common deductions include federal income tax withholding, Social Security tax (6.2%), Medicare tax (1.45%), state income tax withholding, local taxes in some areas, and any benefits or retirement deductions your employer offers.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">What is the Social Security wage base for 2025?<span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-answer">The Social Security wage base for 2025 is $176,100. Once your year-to-date wages exceed this amount, Social Security tax stops for the remainder of the year. Medicare tax has no wage base limit.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">What is Additional Medicare Tax?<span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-answer">An additional 0.9% Medicare tax applies to wages above $200,000 for a single filer. Employers are required to withhold this once wages exceed that threshold in a year, regardless of your filing status.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">How do pre-tax deductions reduce my taxes?<span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-answer">Pre-tax deductions like traditional 401(k) contributions and health insurance premiums reduce the portion of your paycheck subject to federal income tax withholding. This lowers your taxable pay and therefore your estimated withholding, increasing your net pay.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">Why is this estimate different from my actual paycheck?<span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-answer">Actual paycheck amounts vary based on your specific Form W-4 settings, employer payroll system, benefit elections, local taxes, bonuses, overtime, rounding, and other payroll adjustments. This calculator provides a simplified estimate.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">Can I adjust my withholding to get a bigger paycheck?<span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-answer">Yes. You can submit an updated Form W-4 to your employer to adjust your federal withholding. Reducing withholding increases your take-home pay each period but may result in a smaller refund or a balance owed at tax time.</div>
          </div>
